{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Following Willmott et al. (2018) and Stevens et al. (2022), the final question of our jury instructions asked the jurors to rate their confidence in their final decision in the case on a scale of 1-5, with 5 meaning extremely confident and 1 meaning not at all confident.",
    "Once we had drafts of our jury instructions, we piloted the survey for our sample complaint (which contained the Securities Act charges) on an individual without legal knowledge, noting the amount of time it took him to complete the survey and any confusion during the process.",
    "This led us to amend the instructions slightly: for example, they were edited to specify, in question four, that the plaintiff needed to have suffered financial damages specifically.",
    "Table 2 includes questions for each of our charges (excluding the background information).",
    "Our complete, final jury instructions can be found in \"Appendix 7\"."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Following Willmott et al. (2018) and Stevens et al. (2022), the final question of our jury instructions asked the jurors to rate their confidence in their final decision in the case on a scale of 1-5, with 5 meaning extremely confident and 1 meaning not at all confident."
  ]
}